that, assuming equal efficacy between the 2 regimens, there was no threshold 
completion rate for RZ at which the 2 treatments would be of equal net cost. 
Under most circumstances, treatment of latent tuberculosis infection with 
isoniazid is cost-saving than treatment with RZ.

