nails. Prostheses, which are always cemented, are assembled using bipolar cups; 
cases where lysis is so wide on the cotyloid side as to require THR are rare. 
The cotyles, in cases such as these, are those that allow for anchoring with 
several sites (Octopus type), the McMinn or, at times, common cotyles in PE.

